#Constants Explained

#Variables have values that CAN change
#Constants have vaules that CANNOT change
#Variables are written in lower case
#Constants are written in FULL CAPS!

#Example of a constant:
FREE_THROW = 1 # <-- A free throw is ALWAYS 1 point
THREE_POINTER = 3
PI = 3.141592653...

#Definition:
#A constant is a named location
#In a computers memory
#That stores a value
#that value SHOULD NOT be changed
